    <section id="id1164965111748">
      <title>[LO 5.2.2]</title>
      <para id="id1164965049948">Today we are going to practise putting events into the correct order. The boy in this story is very clever! His name is Danny. He saw a sheep trapped on a ledge. He had to rescue it, or it might have fallen off the ledge and drowned in the sea. He used these six things to rescue the sheep: an apple; cotton; tree at top of cliff; walking stick; strong rope; heavy log. </para>
      <para id="id1164965248272">Study the pictures below very carefully to see what Danny did.</para>
      <para id="id1164974814373">
        <figure id="id1164964598806">
          <media id="id1164964598806_media" alt="">
            <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/Picture 1-9f67.png" id="id1164964598806__onlineimage" height="603" width="558"/>
          </media>
        </figure>
      </para>
      <para id="id1164974367522">After you have studied the pictures, read the sentences below. Rewrite them in the correct order.</para>
      <list id="id1164966688350" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>He tied the walking stick to one end of the rope.</item>
        <item>When the sheep was eating the apple, Danny lowered the walking stick very slowly down the cliff.</item>
        <item>Danny put the rope over a branch of the tree.</item>
        <item>He hooked the walking stick under the sheep's horns.</item>
        <item>Danny tied the apple to the cotton.</item>
        <item>The log fell down the cliff and the sheep was pulled up.</item>
        <item>Danny tied the heavy log to the other end of the rope.</item>
        <item>He lowered the apple down to the sheep.</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1164968700514">9. He pushed the heavy log off the cliff.</para>
