    <section id="id1164967307915">
      <title>Memorandum</title>
      <para id="id1164965253127">In this activity, learners are asked to look at a series of pictures and the sentences that go with them. Once they have studied the pictures carefully, they should be able to order the sentences so that the story makes sense. Once again, this activity could also be done in a group or in partners. It would be advisable to discuss the pictures and to read through the sentences with the class before allowing them to begin.</para>
      <para id="id1164968977507">The sequence should be:</para>
      <list id="id1164966765223" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>Danny tied the apple to the cotton.</item>
        <item>Danny put the rope over a branch of the tree.</item>
        <item>He tied the walking stick to one end of the rope.</item>
        <item>Danny tied the heavy log to the other end of the rope.</item>
        <item>He lowered the apple down to the sheep.</item>
        <item>When the sheep was eating the apple, Danny lowered the walking stick very slowly down the cliff.</item>
        <item>He hooked the walking stick under the sheep's horns.</item>
        <item>He pushed the heavy log off the cliff.</item>
        <item>The log fell down the cliff and the sheep was pulled up.</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1164965252484">Make use of the Educator’s Assessment Chart to complete your assessment.</para>
